In a phone call with President Lee of the Republic of Korea, President Obama expressed solidarity with South Korea after an attack by North Korea on the island of Yeonpyeoung. Obama condemned the attack, which resulted in the deaths of at least two Koreans and numerous injuries, and conveyed the thoughts and prayers of the American people. He called on North Korea to cease its provocative actions and adhere to the terms of the Armistice Agreement and international law. The United States pledged unwavering support for its ally, South Korea, and vowed to collaborate with the international community to denounce North Korea's actions and promote peace and security in the region. The two presidents agreed to conduct joint military exercises and enhance training to emphasize their commitment to cooperation and regional stability.